<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>This class will check if a <link linkend="_classcom_1_1thealgorithms_1_1datastructures_1_1trees_1_1_binary_tree">BinaryTree</link> is balanced. A balanced binary tree is defined as a binary tree where the differenced in height between the left and right subtree of each node differs by at most one.</para>

<para>This can be done in both an iterative and recursive fashion. Below, <computeroutput><link linkend="_classcom_1_1thealgorithms_1_1datastructures_1_1trees_1_1_check_if_binary_tree_balanced_1a8f768e75190f9d8e39eef48b71037389">isBalancedRecursive()</link></computeroutput> is implemented in a recursive fashion, and <computeroutput><link linkend="_classcom_1_1thealgorithms_1_1datastructures_1_1trees_1_1_check_if_binary_tree_balanced_1a7f2b9b030c04aba995064b2daefe641c">isBalancedIterative()</link></computeroutput> is implemented in an iterative fashion.</para>

